SECOND CALL FOR PAPERS

In the UNILOG'2010 (Lisbon, April 18-25, 2010) there'll be a Special Sess=
ion on
categorical logic (April 22-25).

Topics that  fit this Special Session include, but are not limited to, th=
e
following:

Relationships between logic and geometry in a topos-theoretic setting
Categorical logic and Categorical foundations of mathematics
Sketch theory; diagrammatic syntax
Functorial semantics and Categorical Model theory
Quantum logic categorically
Extensions of categorical semantics to different kinds of logics, such as=
 modal
and substructural logics
Comparison of different categorical frameworks

The deadline for sending (abstracts of) contributed papers to UNILOG'2010=
 is now
extended to November 15, 2009. Please send your contributions to Valeria =
de
Paiva ( valeria.depaiva@gmail.com )and Andrei Rodin (rodin@ens.fr) . More
information about the Special Session on categorical logic can be found o=
n the
UNILOG'2010 website http://www.uni-log.org in the rubric "Sessions".




